commit.message:
Fix uninitialized is_unsigned flag in P6num

A num without explicit size had an uninitialized is_unsigned flag
causing at least flapping tests in NQP.

Slightly optimize creating backtraces

Instead of using snprintf just to convert a number into a C string and
then converting that C string into an MVMString, just use MVM_coerce_u_s
to convert the number directly an MVMString.

commit.message: Oops, add a JIT coerce_un implementation
Address nine++'s comments

Fix a segfault when building NQP or Rakudo

No idea why it happens though.
Some misc spesh *_u op additions
Some misc JIT *_u op additions
More getattr(s)?ref_u stuff
Add some missing *_u op handling in nativecall code
Add some *_u op handling in reprs
Add some sp_*_u ops

Add uint handling for getdynlex

Now `raku -e 'my uint $*b = 3'` dies with `Cannot modify an immutable
Int (0)`, same as `my int $*b = 3`, instead of `invalid register type in
getdynlex: 20`.

Add missing *_u ops to profiler and analysis tools

Fixes a segfault when running
`raku --profile -e 'my uint $sum = 0; for ^1_000_000 -> uint $i { $sum += $i }; say $sum;'`.

Add getattrsref_u and getlexref_nu ops

They seem to have been missed when the initial round of *_u ops were
created.
